title: Now a former WWE champion says he thinks the world could be flat | For The Win
text:
Now a former WWE champion says he thinks the world could be flat Now a former WWE champion says he thinks the world could be flat Now a former WWE champion says he thinks the world could be flat By Josh Barnett February 22, 2017 2:34 pm shares email By: Josh Barnett | February 22, 2017 2:34 pm 
Amid the Kyrie Irving furor at the NBA All-Star Game suggesting that the Earth is flat, former WWE champion A.J. Styles says the theory should not be discounted. 
During Tuesday’s episode of Talking Smack on WWE Network, Smackdown Live general manager Daniel Bryan asked Styles if he wanted to talk about being a “flat Earther.” 
“I’m not a ‘flat-earther’,” Styles said. “I’m just saying there is some stuff about it that makes sense. I don’t think you can handle it.” 
Bryan explained to Styles that the Earth was a sphere and host Renee Young talked about how the earth spins on its axis. More Kyrie Irving!
